,Not Recommended,434420,34716915,Posted: 3 September,all,TeddyStyle,"The Chosen RPG is a short RPG maker game, that honestly has had bits and pieces of every RPG maker game I have ever played and reviewed. The question is if the bits and pieces are the right ones and if it is put together in a nice game.The story starts off with a lot of backstory and lore to get you into the story. The stereotypical, there is a legend that needs to be fulfilled, they tried to diffrentiate with making the characters as if they are straight from an anime. What also makes it a complete stereotype is that the character does not acknowlegde him being part of the legend until almost the very end. The story would be less linear if there was multiple enemies trying to stop you in your 'quest'. Well quest is not the right way to say this, since the game is another find along as you go RPG. I remember playing this game for a little and coming back after a few days and completely forgetting what the objective was without any way to figure out, without spoiling the game by checking a playthrough, how to continue it. The story turned out to be pretty decent but right as I was getting into it, it ended. After this they gave the classic, ""to be continued..."", hinting towards a sequel.The battle sequences have the classic background, enemies and fighting style. Added along to this is pretty nice music and battle animatuons from both sides which is a pretty nice but small feature that you don't see much from RPG maker games. The things they kept from the RPG maker package is that the enemies have no healthbar, which is a nice feature but not mandatory, also the effects like balance, poison, blind, paralyse, sleep and many more. The combat would be way better if they payed more attention to the balancing in general. For story purposes you start off with the 3rd best sword in the game, which in the end 'evolves' into the best sword in the game, which makes you start off with a giant advantage. The difficulty is on point in the beginning, the back to back challenges made it very intense to play, afterwards once you got better items it turned out to be way too easy. For the people who enjoy grinding, you will get satisfied. Aside from one boss which you can battle over and over, seems like a bug honestly, you have a training hall where you can battle different tiers of monsters to your liking. The training hall also has an unique boss that gives you second best sword in the game once you beat it. Honestly that boss was harder than the final battle which is pretty sad.Concluding a verdict for this game with a yes or no rating is a challenging thing to do. It keeps showing itself in a good spotlight but gets pulled down again by the things missing in this game. They hinted pretty hard at a potential sequel but I see a lot of space for improvement. The story could have been in one game but they have many opportunities to go into with the sequel. If you are a fan of RPG's, take a quick look at this before you instantly buy this. If you don't like the anime theme or need a challenge you should look towards other games."
