,Recommended,434420,23672144,"Posted: 20 June, 2016",all,Fligglebleh,"I bought this game on sale in a pack of similar old-school RPGs for less than $1. While this game, along with its siblings, aren't old-school as far as time goes, they are in spirit and in style.To be honest, after beating two out of the 5 purchased, this one is my favorite so far, and well-worth the buy. I'm actually only posting this review since it received so many negative reviews recently, and I think it may be due to lack of perspective on the reviewer's part.The Chosen RPG, unlock some others of its kind, is a bit more in-depth regarding stats and equipment. Like some more modern RPGs on mobile devices or on portables, you can optimize your equipment quickly for the gamer-on-the-go, and there's more than just the minimum 4 stats that some RPGs have.The graphics aren't great, but if you're an experienced gamer who grew up with worse, then they're about on-par when considering the RPG Maker engine. Yes, the most detailed of the graphics mostly include scantilly-clad women with erect nipples, take that as a positive (if you're into that) or a negative (like other recent reviewers), but either way the game mechanics are more streamlined than others of its kind available on steam and if this game was made back in the 90s when these types were more popular, it could have been a serious trend-setter.Really this game is a matter of perspective; if you expect to spend $2 (or less, like me) then you should usually expect a game of slightly lesser caliber, or at least equal to this one's.Overall, this game has been a positive experience for me, and I've enjoyed it more than similar titles."
