,Recommended,434420,29907591,Posted: 13 February,all,mighty hawk | TradeSkinsFast.com,"OverallThis is a fun little RPG. While fairly similar to most games made in the RPG Maker, it's still pretty entertaining. I've listed some pros and cons down below.ProsLanguage - The English in the game is grammatically correct almost everywhere. I've seen very few mistakes.Story - Even after only 1 hour, I'm still intrigued by the story. It almost makes you not want to stop playing.Trading Cards - I bought this game mainly to boost my Steam level. I've calculated that it would only cost me 1,75€ to get the game AND enough trading cards to get the badge to level 5 (NOTE: I got the game on sale for 0,22€). After the 3 card drops, the game itself had actually earned itself, if you look at the value of those three cards.Music - The game offers some very calm and pleasant music, that's caused me to be really calm and comfortable writing this review. You'd almost think that I've been hypnotised by the music to write a positive review.Items - The game offers a wide variety of items. All from armors and weapons, over health, mana and poison curity potions, to special 'artifacts' that can unlock secrets and easter-eggs throughout the game.ConsNudity - While no characters are fully naked, the game has been tagged 'Nudity'. Multiple female characters are also partially nude, which is something completely unneccesary if you ask me. It *almost* partially ruins the game, but it's see-through. That shouldn't stop you from buying the game.Swear words - There are a few bad words, which I definitely think is unneccary. The bad language does not boost the game in any way, and it's a minor setback if you ask me.ConclusionIf you are looking for a fun little RPG, you should definitely get this. If you're looking for easy and cheap XP for your Steam profile (507 XP for a minimum of 1,75€, possibly 2,25€), get this. All 5 trading cards needed to craft one badge costs 0,30€ all-together, while crafting all five badges costs 1,53€.If not for the nudity and swear-words, I'd say you could get this for your kids, I'd guarantee they'd have a lot of fun. Thumbs up."
