,Not Recommended,434420,24287804,"Posted: 12 July, 2016",all,Corrupted Kestrel,"This game isn't great. It also isn't soul-devouringly awful, so hey, at least playing it won't summon a horde of Dementors.Mostly, it just feels like a first draft--like they wrote the story, tossed together the environments, etc., and never bothered to proof it.One example, though minor, is very early on--in the very first dungeon, in fact. There are a bunch of injured/dead people, one of whom, when you speak to her, changes sprites into an old bearded man. I spoke to her several times just to confirm that yes, I really did tee dat puddy tat.Another example is after a specific boss battle; the boss never disappears, and speaking to it again will repeat the battle. I only did so once, by accident, but it seems to be an infinite loop.As for the rest...to keep from making this review way too long, I'll just sum up the problems:-It's full of glitches (though at least not game-breaking ones, in my experience) and has a general lack of polish.-Each party member, barring the (male) MC, goes around in nothing but her underwear. I was genuinely surprised when I met a female NPC with a portrait who was actually wearing clothes.-There is no quest log, so heaven help you if you aren't paying attention or forget where you're supposed to go.-It is in desperate need of a proofreader. Those commas are so spliced they feel like they just escaped from Rapture. There are also many typos and other errors.-It ends abruptly on a cliffhanger, complete with ""To Be Continued"". YMMV if you mind cliffhangers or not, but the ending really is quite sudden.Despite all that, the gameisstill fun; I just can't say I recommend it."
