,Recommended,434420,31851958,Posted: 19 May,all,Zyke,"I found the game a solid, but not amazing JRPG style RPGmaker experience.Pros:+Short enough to beat, long enough to enjoy. The game doesn't drag on, or waste a lot of time so you can enjoy it for what it is and move on with your life.+Enough Hidden and optional areas and items to scratch that explorer itch. There's your standard potions in dressers, but finding that first hidden treasure room felt great.+ Game is good about keeping you informed of your objective, some might say too straight forward or linear, I say I don't mind a reminder of where the game wants me to go next.Nuetral::the Art is what it is, don't like RPG Maker art, or girls in underwear, then its a minus if you do its a plus. I will say in combat the titalating aspect of the art is less noticable, and I appreciated that the attack animations reflect your changing weapons even if the animations themselves are a bit underwhelming. Enemy sprites are also big and well done overall.:Combat is also a bit hit or miss. early on I liked old school JRPG turn based style, later on I thought boss enemies were unthreatening sacks of HP. Outside of when I explored areas I out of order only 1 enemy even KO'd a single party member.Cons:-The writing isn't great, and the characters don't get much depth. Most characters get 1-2 lines from an NPC in their village explaining how they were eiled for using magic or were orphaned. At best I'd call it servicable, and it doesn't drag on too long. Don't expect any huge emotional reveals or heart to hearts, or changes in motivation. the game tells its story simple and directly-Bit easy overall. Most ""puzzles"" could be brute forced with trial and error, random encounters don't really tax your mana or resources, and for most of the game the hero's weapon is significantly better than anythign his party members can do.- Couple scripting/event bugs where boss enemies would respawn or fight you again if you talked to them instead of leaving the room, and other inconsistencies of that sort.In conclusion, I enjoyed the game for what it was, the pet peeves i had overall were minor, and the game was short enough that I beat it before it over stayed its welcome."
