,Recommended,434420,21552629,"Posted: 29 February, 2016",all,moose_irl,"Based on the reviews, I expected this to be pretty terrible. It's actually a pretty decent, if simple, RPG. I got it with a coupon, so I paid something like 70cents. That's pretty good for a game that I got a solid four hours of gameplay out of (my registered time is much higher, I played this mostly during work). The art is nice and the music is fine. Yes, it could do with some more world expanding, but there were a fair amount of enemies and enough 'quests' to keep from getting repetative. The small map was disappointing, but it did pretty well with the limited space. The story was your generic JRPG-style plot, but there's nothing wrong with that. I'm not sure why the girls were all in underwear, but it's not like that detracted from the story at all.If you want a casual, short, cheap RPG to waste a few hours on, I'd say this is well worth it, especially on sale."
